title: Poss. lenticel rot of potatoes
description:
Scot Nelson posted a photo:

Lenticel rot of potato tubers is caused by the bacterium Erwinia carotovora subsp. carotovora. The disease has become an economically important post-harvest disease for some growers. Disease symptoms are sunken and rotted tissue surrounding tuber lenticels that develop after harvest and packing.

An alternative pathogen in this case could be Colletotrichum coccodes, a fungus, as the symptoms depicted in this image are somewhat consistent with the disease caused by that organism.

Lab testing is needed to determine the disease etiology.
author: nobody@flickr.com (Scot Nelson)
tags: potato solanum lesions tuberosum lenticelrot
